                                    Combined Defence Services Examination is conducted, twice a year by the Union Public Service Commission, for Recruitment into the Indian Military Academy, Officers’ Training Academy, Indian Naval Academy and Indian Air Force Academy. CDS Selection Process
                                    encompasses two stages i.e. Written test and SSB Interview round. In the first stage (written exam), candidates have to attempt three papers for selection in IMA , INA and AFA whereas OTA candidates have to attempt
                                    only 2 papers. In the second stage of selection, they have to appear for an Interview which will test their intelligence, personality and psychological aptitude. In order to be eligible for CDS candidate has to qualify
                                    both stage 1 and stage 2.
                                </p>
                                <br/>
